   3.920384989925045*^9, 3.920385116048703*^9},
 CellLabel->"In[16]:=",
 CellID->766743590,ExpressionUUID->"5ded5f29-a5e7-4b5f-98aa-5ce489c38dca"],

Cell["\<\
We can look for and remove any \[Pi] phase discontinuities.  In this case, we \
find that all of the phase changes between adjacent points are small, with an \
average value similar to the standard deviation.  In the optional plot, \
values near zero would indicate a \[Pi] phase change, while values near \[Pi] \
indicate a very smoothly changing phase.\
\>", "ExampleText",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.9203845041048517`*^9, 3.9203846406669273`*^9}, {
  3.9203846795918407`*^9, 3.920384718306408*^9}, {3.920384755583188*^9, 
  3.9203848057499857`*^9}, {3.920384860654337*^9, 3.920384911794429*^9}, {
  3.920384943346965*^9, 3.920384965914321*^9}, {3.9203851639593782`*^9, 
  3.9203852102345867`*^9}, {3.9203853097464933`*^9, 3.9203854785264587`*^9}, {
  3.920385564164176*^9, 3.92038559825028*^9}, {3.920732500663156*^9, 
  3.920732503658801*^9}, {3.920964929311368*^9, 3.9209649308626413`*^9}, {
  3.982743555715757*^9, 3.982743682549074*^9}, {3.98274415511906*^9, 
  3.982744181175089*^9}, {3.982744436012334*^9, 3.98274445860251*^9}},
 CellID->761617463,ExpressionUUID->"540aeffc-62ca-42d7-99d6-727bdbd47a95"],

